      <section eId="sec_CHC-1239-1">
        <num>CHC 1239.1</num>
        <heading>1239.1.  Reporting requirement; statistical availability</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1239-1__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>For each adopted child, the court shall ensure that the department receives all of
the following information:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1239-1__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Whether either of the adopted parents are related to the child.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1239-1__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The age of the child at placement.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1239-1__subsec_A__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The age of the child at the time of finalization.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1239-1__subsec_A__subsec_4">
            <num>(4)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The gender of the child.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1239-1__subsec_A__subsec_5">
            <num>(5)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The race of the child.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1239-1__subsec_A__subsec_6">
            <num>(6)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The location of placement.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1239-1__subsec_A__subsec_7">
            <num>(7)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Other nonidentifying information the department requests in order to maintain
statistical records of adoption finalizations.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1239-1__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The department shall release yearly statistics on the adoptions of children in
Louisiana and placement of those children.  These statistics shall be made available to the
public.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=1238166</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
